Four men accused of beating a man at the Rustenburg Recreation Centre were expected to appear in the Rustenburg Magistrates Court on Wednesday. Wayne Mynhard, 26, Hatting Stephen, 24, Armand van Niekerk, 22, and Ooshuizen Hengardt, 29, allegedly attacked Siyakudumisa Nkula at the recreation centre on August 26, in what was believed to be a racially motivated attack. The four were charged with assault with the intention to do grievous bodily harm, and have been out on R500 bail each. African News Agency (ANA)